===Verb===
{{en-verb|pays|paying|'''[[paid]]''' or '''[[payed]]'''}}

# {{transitive}} To [[give]] [[money]] or other compensation to in exchange for goods or services.
#: ''He '''paid''' him to clean the place up.''
#: ''He '''paid''' her off the books and in kind where possible.''
# {{transitive}} To discharge, as a debt or other obligation, by giving or doing what is due or required.
#: ''He offered to '''pay''' the bill.''
#: ''He has '''paid''' his debt to society.''
# {{transitive}} To discharge a debt by delivering (money owed).
#: ''He still has to '''pay''' a fifty euro fine.''
# {{transitive}} To be profitable for.
#: ''It didn't '''pay''' him to keep the store open any more.''
# {{transitive}} To [[give]] (something else than money).
#: ''To '''pay''' attention''
# {{intransitive}} To be [[profitable]].
#: ''Crime doesn’t '''pay'''''.
# {{intransitive}} To discharge an obligation or debt.
#: ''He was allowed to go as soon as he '''paid'''.''
# {{intransitive}} To suffer consequences.
#: ''He '''paid''' for his fun in the sun with a terrible sunburn.''

